# This command I use it for enable Ingress control, to be able to access the application out of local exploring.

For Minikube, you can enable the NGINX Ingress controller:

```
 minikube addons enable ingress
```


# Verify the Ingress controller is running:

kubectl get pods -n kube-system





If PostgreSQL is running in a Kubernetes pod:
Check the Environment Variables: If your PostgreSQL pod is running with environment variables for the database credentials, you can inspect them using the following:
```
kubectl exec -it <postgres-pod-name> -n <namespace> -- env

```
